      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "jupyter: python3\n",
        "title: \"Parameter Exploration\"\n",
        "---"
      ],
      "id": "8ef58105"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "collapse": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: setup\n",
        "import bsplot\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "from tvbo import Dynamics, SimulationExperiment\n",
        "from tvbo.datamodel.schema import Exploration, ExplorationAxis\n",
        "\n",
        "bsplot.style.use(\"tvbo\")"
      ],
      "id": "setup",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Sweeping parameters declaratively\n",
        "\n",
        "In Chapter 1 we changed parameters by re-instantiating the `Dynamics`. That is fine for one or two values, but it scales badly. TVBO has a first-class metadata object for this: `Exploration`.\n",
        "\n",
        "An `Exploration` lives on `experiment.explorations` and is dispatched by the backend when you call `.run()`.\n",
        "\n",
        "## A one-axis sweep\n",
        "\n",
        "We take the `Generic2dOscillator` and sweep its bifurcation parameter `a` across five values."
      ],
      "id": "40c8a214"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "model = Dynamics.from_db(\"Generic2dOscillator\")\n",
        "\n",
        "exp = SimulationExperiment(dynamics=model)\n",
        "exp.integration.duration = 800       # ms\n",
        "exp.integration.step_size = 0.01      # ms\n",
        "\n",
        "exp.explorations[\"a_sweep\"] = Exploration(\n",
        "    name=\"a_sweep\",\n",
        "    space=ExplorationAxis(parameter=\"a\", explored_values=[-2.0, -1.0, 0.0, 1.0, 2.0]),\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "result = exp.run(\"tvboptim\")"
      ],
      "id": "ddd402fc",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "The result keeps the same shape conventions as a single simulation, with one extra axis for the swept parameter:"
      ],
      "id": "b2e4fa67"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sweep = result.explorations[\"a_sweep\"]\n",
        "print(\"results shape:\", sweep.results.shape, \"  axis:\", sweep.axes[0].name)"
      ],
      "id": "aa32e950",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "`Exploration.plot()` overlays the trajectories. Increasing `a` walks the system through a Hopf bifurcation: from a stable focus to a sustained limit cycle."
      ],
      "id": "2a9e18a3"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sweep.plot(overlay=True)"
      ],
      "id": "bbfe66cb",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Trial-based exploration\n",
        "\n",
        "The same object also drives Monte-Carlo style replication via `n_trials`. Each trial uses different initial conditions and (if noise is configured) different noise realisations."
      ],
      "id": "fdcabd77"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "from tvbo.datamodel.schema import Distribution, Range\n",
        "# exp.explorations.clear()\n",
        "\n",
        "exp.dynamics.state_variables['V'].distribution = Distribution(domain=Range(lo=-1, hi=1))\n",
        "exp.dynamics.state_variables['W'].initial_value = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "exp.explorations[\"trials\"] = Exploration(name=\"trials\", n_trials=10)\n",
        "\n",
        "result = exp.run(\"tvb\")\n",
        "result.explorations[\"trials\"].plot(overlay=True)"
      ],
      "id": "9ea665da",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Recap\n",
        "\n",
        "- `exp.explorations[name] = Exploration(...)` declares a sweep â€” never assign a plain dict.\n",
        "- `ExplorationAxis(parameter=..., explored_values=[...])` defines the axis.\n",
        "- `n_trials=N` runs `N` randomised replicates.\n",
        "- The backend (`tvboptim`) vectorises the sweep automatically; nothing else changes.\n",
        "\n",
        "The next chapter takes the same `Dynamics` object and replaces brute-force sweeping with **continuation**, which tracks equilibria and limit cycles directly."
      ],
      "id": "f623aa24"
    }
  ],
